# Vibecoding Project Cheatsheet

## Overview

Personal Money Management App for tracking expenses via CSV bank statement imports.

## Tech Stack

- **Build:** Vite + React 18 + TypeScript
- **State:** Jotai with localStorage persistence
- **UI:** Chakra UI v3 + Tailwind CSS
- **Charts:** Nivo (pie, bar)
- **Utilities:** papaparse (CSV), date-fns (dates), uuid (IDs)

## Features

- CSV bank statement import with drag-and-drop
- Expense categorization with keyword auto-matching
- Date range filtering with quick presets
- Expense breakdown pie chart by category
- Monthly spending trend bar chart
- Transaction list with category assignment

## Data Models

```typescript
type Transaction = {
  id: string
  date: Date
  description: string
  amount: number          // negative = expense, positive = income
  categoryId: string | null
}

type Category = {
  id: string
  name: string
  color: string
  keywords: string[]      // for auto-categorization
}

type DateFilter = {
  startDate: Date
  endDate: Date
}
```

## File Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── csvUpload.tsx          # File upload with drag-and-drop
│   ├── transactionList.tsx    # Filterable transaction table
│   ├── expensePieChart.tsx    # Expense breakdown by category
│   ├── trendChart.tsx         # Monthly spending bar chart
│   ├── dateRangePicker.tsx    # Date period selector
│   └── dashboard.tsx          # Main dashboard layout
├── store/
│   ├── transactionsAtom.ts    # Transactions with localStorage sync
│   ├── filteredTransactionsAtom.ts
│   └── dateFilterAtom.ts      # Current date range
├── utils/
│   ├── csvParser.ts           # Parse CSV to transactions
│   └── formatters.ts          # Date/currency formatting
├── types/
│   └── index.ts               # TypeScript type definitions
└── App.tsx                    # App shell
```

## Commands

- `pnpm tsc` - TypeScript type checking
- `pnpm unit` - Run Jest tests
- `pnpm dev` - Start dev server




